                            <comment id="157702" author="simmonsja" created="Tue, 5 Jul 2016 18:34:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes its a duplicate except this is requested for b2_8.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="152502" author="adilger" created="Tue, 17 May 2016 01:06:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Seems that this is a known issue and is being worked on in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8117&quot; title=&quot;lustre-ppc fails to build on ppc64 el7&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-8117&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-8117&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="147666" author="adilger" created="Sat, 2 Apr 2016 03:21:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Have you looked at what was reported at the end of &lt;tt&gt;config.log&lt;/tt&gt; as requested above?  We build the master branch for arch &lt;tt&gt;ppc64&lt;/tt&gt; every day, but it seems that we do not build the b2_8 release ranch. Also, we build for RHEL6.6 and not RHEL7.2, so there may be some errors we aren&apos;t seeing. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="147661" author="jimmy316@gmail.com" created="Sat, 2 Apr 2016 00:18:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am trying to build PPC rpm&apos;s on RH7.2 I get the following error &lt;br/&gt;
checking for /usr/src/kernels/3.10.0-327.el7.ppc64le/include/generated/autoconf.h... yes&lt;br/&gt;
checking for /usr/src/kernels/3.10.0-327.el7.ppc64le/include/linux/version.h... yes&lt;br/&gt;
checking for /usr/src/kernels/3.10.0-327.el7.ppc64le/include/linux/kconfig.h... yes&lt;br/&gt;
checking for cross compilation... no&lt;br/&gt;
checking for external module build target... M&lt;br/&gt;
checking that modules can be built at all... no&lt;br/&gt;
configure: error: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Kernel modules cannot be built. Consult config.log for details.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you are trying to build with a kernel-source rpm,&lt;br/&gt;
consult build/README.kernel-source&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;I can succesfully build the binaries and run make install just cannot build rpm&apos;s for shipping. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
